Luiz moved to PSG from Chelsea in 2014 for £50million but will hope to get the better of his former club

PSG are in town to face Premier League leaders Chelsea as they go head to head in the Champions League

Luiz posted the snap after warning Chelsea they won't achieve success by simply sitting back when the two sides meet.

The first leg of the Champions League tie ended 1-1, meaning a goalless draw would be enough to send Jose Mourinho's side through to the next round.

But Luiz feels it would be foolish of his old club to invite pressure on themselves, considering the strength of the Ligue 1 champions' attacking options. 

'I know how Jose (Mourinho) will prepare for this, he will be telling the boys to be patient and hit us on the counter attack,' Luiz told The Mirror.

'He knows that we need to score and that they don't, I know that is his way. We must be careful because I know that Chelsea have the ability to hurt on the counter attack, but they must be careful as well.

'To sit back and just defend against Zlatan (Ibrahimovic), (Edinson) Cavani and (Ezequiel) Lavezzi can also be very dangerous, so it is not just us who have to be careful.' 

